reviews.text: It is Sunday, let us seize the means of relaxation. I was outside the whole week and needed a Sunday reset while in MN. A coworker of mine recommended this spot and it lived up to the hype. I could tell the a√ßa√≠ bowl was made with love and each ingredient was fresh. Loved the mural inside and the small table outside so I can fully relax on this Sunday

Love coming here! The staff is SUPER nice, friendly, and always helping me make the best choices!! I love their juices, protein smoothies, and their vibe. Super cute, plants, colorful, and very cheery energy! Sign up for their texts, seriously, they give you very generous discounts that you and your pocket book will love to take advantage of!

I went here because a friend and I are on a smoothie/salad diet. So, I thought I'd check this place out.  The fruit and vegetable quality and cleanliness is on point. They have specials on Buddha bowls I think Tuesday and Thursdays? The place is very clean and the staff are really nice. I wish they had a couple of more options for salad dressings like a cumin based taco flavored one and maybe a French one. It's also a comfortable eat in cafe and offers a clean restroom. It's not for the faint of wallet, but the quality to me, is worth my heath and wellness any day. Plus, I feel really good after I eat here too. Check it out.

I come & grab smoothies here often. Smoothies are delicious & service is awesome. Gabriel in particular is a wonderful person. Always greets me with a warm welcome. I really appreciate his kindness & services. God bless him & Vibe Organic!
My Glow Green smoothie was delicious! The staff was super friendly when I came in and the place is so cute!

Lawd knows it is hard enough not to opt for quick and easily aquired junk when out and about,  especially when one typically has zero options for a wiser choice. Zero customer service skills.

Update: As a multi-race minority woman myself, it would be nice when spending my hard earned money to buy a smoothie, to be treated with a shred of quality and friendly customer service while doing so.
Unfortunately, I did not receive this in my visit at this establishment by 2 separate employees, as told by the manager herself ‚Äúhe does not speak English, he‚Äôs Brazilian‚Äù when referring to the gentleman manning the cash register, who was unable to answer questions about the menu/ product being sold or if cash is accepted as a form of payment & the young female employee whom had a nasty attitude when we could not hear her mumbling under the overhead music playing, that our smoothies were ready at the counter. To then proceed and say to me after grabbing our smoothies despite the confusion. ‚ÄúNext time try getting up to get your smoothies and hear better‚Äù while rolling her eyes.
Somehow these incidents of poor customer service that we experienced did not make it into the owners response to my review.
I appreciate that my money was refunded for one of the two smoothies that were purchased after asking the manager for our money back.
Although, had some accountability been taken for the blatant rudeness on the employees part from the employee, managers or owner, I would not have felt the need to share my negative experience on this public forum.
Since this review, Alex, another manager at this establishment called me directly after leaving my information for the Owner to reach out.
Alex listened to my neg. experience and told me he‚Äôd have a staff meeting.
Hopefully, this step by management will assist in fostering more adequate customer service skills for staff and a better overall customer experience for ALL customers.
